# UI/UX Design Rules (Vibe-Coder v3.0)

## Component Search Order (MANDATORY)
1. `COMBINED/ui-design/ui-components-galaxy/` → 3,000+ components
2. `COMBINED/ui-design/ui-components-shadcn/` → accessible React components
3. `COMBINED/ui-design/ui-impeccable/` → 18 design cmds + 7 refs + anti-pattern detection
4. `COMBINED/ui-design/ui-taste-skill/` → 7 premium skills, 3-dial parameterization (DESIGN_VARIANCE, MOTION_INTENSITY, VISUAL_DENSITY)
5. `COMBINED/ui-design/ui-stitch-skills/` → Google Stitch design generation, React components, DESIGN.md
6. `COMBINED/ui-design/ui-rules/ui-ux-pro-max/` → 161 design rules
7. Custom → only if 1-6 have nothing; document why

## Anti-Slop (Impeccable)
- NO gray text on white backgrounds
- NO Inter font as default
- NO purple gradients everywhere
- NO nested cards inside cards
- NO bounce easing on everything
- Run: `/impeccable:audit` to detect AI design slop

## Critical Rules (auto-check these)
- Contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for normal text
- Touch targets ≥ 44×44pt (48×48dp Android)
- Focus rings (2-4px) on ALL interactive elements
- No emoji as icons — use SVG (Heroicons, Lucide)
- Mobile-first design, breakpoints: 375/768/1024/1440
- 4pt/8dp spacing system
- Animations 150-300ms with ease-out, respect prefers-reduced-motion
- font-display: swap for web fonts
- Images: WebP/AVIF with width/height for CLS prevention

